title: What songs prominently feature nonsense words? - Quora

response.answer_text: “De Do Do Do, De Da Da Da” by the Police:  “Witch Doctor” by David Seville:  “Hooked on a Feeling” by Blue Swede:  “The Lion Sleeps Tonight” by the Tokens:  “Louie Louie” by the Kingsmen:  “Da Doo Ron Ron” by the Crystals:  “Doo Wah Diddy Diddy” by Manfred Mann:  “Tutti Frutti” by Little Richard:  “MMMBop” by Hanson:  “Blue Moon” by the Marcels:  “Bawitdaba” by Kid Rock:

Have a song from 1974 where the lyrics are totally made up from what American rock an roll singers sound like to Italians who don’t speak English.  “Prisencolinensinainciusol” by Adriano Celentano. Going back even further, to the 1950’s, we have the comedy song  “The Ying Tong Song” by The Goons. The goons noticed the proliferation of aphorisms, mottos and slogans in post war Britain (“Go to work on an egg”, “ a little dab’ll do ya”, “Drinka pinta milka day” and dozens of others) and decided to create a total nonsense slogan, slip it into their radio show a few times, and see if it caught on… Boy did it catch on.
